annotation.TEXT: Alright, this level's done. I just wish they'd quit it with the react-within-one-twentieth-of-a-second-or-die thing.
Level 27...
Or, maybe it really is that easy. Who knows?
BGM: Nightwish - Ever Dream
And boom, I'm done just like that!
Sanae demos: 5
Also, on top of the rightmost grounded cannon is a safe spot too.
And here we have our first reused BGM. Also, I remember this puzzle from Goron50's videos. It's one of Bear's favorites!
BGM: Princess Tomato in the Salad Kingdom - Level 8 - Castle (reused again)
Knowing what to do, I should be able to conquer this on my first try. Oh, and Kisume here acts like a Goomba, and the Suwako on the right is basically a Ninji.

Alright. That's one hit. You've gotta hit the ON/OFF block three times total to dump Suwako into the pit. However, make absolutely sure she isn't jumping when you hit the block the second time, or you'll be screwed over!
More reused music, and-- Whoa, holy crap!
Jump into the drip blocks here to start swimming, and hug the cannons on the right while near the ceiling to be safe from the circling spiky guy that's wearing flashing shades it looks like.

Another annoying thing about this new layout is while I'm annotating, and it saves or autosaves, the whole page quickly shifts down a pixel and then back up. It doesn't seem like much, but it bothers me anyway, and makes me wonder why they would have it even do that in the first place! None of the previous layouts shifted like that while saving my annotations!
Maybe I didn't get jinxed here, but there's still two levels left in this row...
Carefully jump into the Yuyuko ring, and hope that a random Yuyuko won't appear at the wrong place at the wrong time for you!

Oh, man. I remember this one from Goron50's videos too. It looks like simple Torpedo Arm hopping, but you can't bounce too high when aiming to land on that cloud on the right, or you'll crash into the torpedo above you!
BGM: Custom - Mimoshiro by MuimiMoji
Made it, although I probably made that look a lot easier than it actually is!
BGM: Custom - Easy Waters by Gpetry
BGM: Final Fantasy 9 - Airship Hilda Garde

Yeah, this is one of the easiest levels in this hack. The bombs can't hurt you through mere contact, and you can easily toss back the ones coming your way before they explode, so you'd have to be playing pretty poorly to blow it here!
Okay, this music is new, and it sounds hauntingly fitting for a ghost level involving Yuyukos!
Hold either left or right when you enter to avoid immediately headbutting the Remilia above you. After that, it's pretty much the same deal as that earlier Cirno level.
I hope there's still plenty of unique music left to be heard in this hack... Anyway, with this one, you can take your time and assess the situation.
Also, I think the slippery terrain is in effect too, which can make it tricky to just stand on the ice blocks.
Reimu, get in there and do it right...
BGM: Csikos Post (reused)
I'm going to try doing a quick kick of the ice block at the boss as soon as he moves close enough...
In fact, it's probably easier, since you don't have to worry about horizontal arrow blocks on the sides. However, these arrow blocks do move up and down, which might make attacking a little trickier.
Level 24...
Whew! I was worried that I'd screw up somehow at the last second!
Or, you could be like Goron50, and cheat death by landing on the extreme corner of a death block, where its deathly properties don't seem to reach...
Whoa, there's a lot of stuff flying around here, including stars being thrown by Marisa. Don't panic, though. This room isn't really that bad, and I believe your start point is a safe spot.
Okay, good! Now, the timing of the third hit doesn't matter, as long as you land the hit... and beat the time limit too! Better hurry!
Okay, time for the last level in this row, level 29...
BGM: Princess Tomato in the Salad Kingdom - Level 8 - Castle (reused)

Also, just like with the Cirno level, you might be able to score a couple double-hits and make this a 1-up combo! (Not that Reimu needs it, as Sanae's been the only unfortunate one in my playthrough so far...)

Huzzah! Now, as soon as you land the third blow, make sure you won't bounce into a death block during the victory sequence. (You don't automatically march to the right, but you will keep your current momentum.)
Level 23...
Now for level 20...
Wow, halfway through this row already. On to level 25...
So, yeah. This level's pretty easy if you're not careless.
Whoa, Lily White, when did you get so destructive? You're so destructive, you're doing most of the work for me!
Level 28...

Good thing I reacted well enough there! After that quick reaction thing, the rest is pretty easy. However, do not touch the creepy Aya heads, as they will kill you on contact. I know this from Goron50's videos.
Also, mind the ceiling when you get to the upper area. It likes to shove you downwards!
Yeah, I'm really angry about YT's stupidity, so I'm going to rant about it, and I think I have every right to rant. Anyway, on to level 22...
Also, be careful with the blocks on the left side of the room. Due to their glitchy nature, it's possible to fall through them while hugging the left wall.
Oh, man. Gotta do some spin jumping acrobatics here...
NOOOOO!!! It was one of those levels where you only get a split-second to react! Yep, I knew I'd get jinxed...

Sweet! I got my bounce height there just right on the first try! Hey, maybe I can complete this whole row of levels without any deaths! (Oh, nuts. I shouldn't have said that. I just know the game's going to screw me over at some point now.)
Whoa! I hit the ceiling there, but it didn't screw me up, fortunately. Also, the random Yuyukos were nice enough to mostly leave me alone here, so I kind of got lucky.
BGM: Alex Kidd in Miracle World - Underwater
Level 26...
BGM: Final Fantasy 9 - Airship Hilda Garde
Ooh, this winding path is starting to stretch pretty far! (I'm told this one eventually leads to the final boss.)
And no, I wasn't going to try touching those yellow circle blocks again. I think it was a complete fluke that I managed to break a level once with them already, so I'm not taking any more chances!
Okay, Sanae, level 21's all you. Let's see if I can avoid having any more YT-related issues while annotating here...
And with that, the third row of levels is complete! Now, let's take a look at the progress I'm making with the paths around the edges of the map...
BGM: Mega Man 3 - Spark Man's Stage

Oh, gee, where have I heard this music before? Anyway, we've got this mummy glasses dude, who's basically a Big Boo Boss. Also, there are random bullets, bouncy blocks, and death blocks. This could be really tough!
Alright, so next time, I'll resume here, with level 30 (and maybe I'll rant about YouTube some more, but we'll see). To be continued...
BGM: Seiken Densetsu 3 - Nuclear Fusion (reused)

Okay, the far right ice block is going to be the toughest, because the boss doesn't move that far to the right, so there's greater risk of a random bullet either hitting me or destroying my ice block.
Welcome back to Hakurei Adventure Mission! All of you that hate it when YouTube forces you to use a page design that you hate, raise your hands!

That upper row of blocks bounces you, but that really shouldn't make any diff-- Oh, boy. The adobe plugin crashed on me as I was typing this annotation, causing Firefox to lock up for about a minute, and forcing me to retype the annotation after I finally got the page refreshed. I blame YouTube's new layout, of course.
